# ── Spotify API credentials ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a free app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#
# When creating the app, Spotify asks for a Redirect URI.
# Use:  http://127.0.0.1:6767
#
# Rules (per developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/concepts/redirect_uri):
#   - localhost is NOT allowed
#   - Must be explicit IPv4/IPv6 loopback with a port: http://127.0.0.1:PORT
#   - The URI is never actually visited; Client Credentials flow never
#     redirects a browser. 6767 matches this project's web UI port.
#
# When asked "Which API/SDKs are you planning to use?", select:
#   ✔ Web API  (only this one — nothing else is needed)
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# ── Music output directory ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute path on your HOST machine that will be mounted into the container
MUSIC_DIR=/absolute/path/to/your/music/folder
